{"by":"nickjj","id":47755015,"parent":47752819,"text":"One nice thing about tmux is it also supports include files in its config.<p>This lets you put your theme colors in a different file, such as `source-file &quot;~&#x2F;.config&#x2F;tmux&#x2F;theme.conf&quot;` and then your theme switching external script or tool can symlink a specific theme&#x27;s tmux file to that path.<p>That&#x27;s what I do in my dotfiles:<p><pre><code>    # Main tmux config\n    https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;nickjj&#x2F;dotfiles&#x2F;blob&#x2F;master&#x2F;.config&#x2F;tmux&#x2F;tmux.conf\n\n    # One of the theme files\n    https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;nickjj&#x2F;dotfiles&#x2F;blob&#x2F;master&#x2F;themes&#x2F;tokyonight-moon&#x2F;tmux.conf\n</code></pre>\nIt allows for hot-reloading different themes as well.","time":1776099951,"type":"comment"}